\f0\b Known issues:\

\f1\b0 \
Because PreceptorTools is a Revolution stack and not an application it should work fine in the Windows environment.  While this version of PreceptorTools is reportedly more compatible with the Windows operating system, it still has not been extensively tested in that OS. There may be bugs of which I am unaware.  More formal testing will commence with the Windows environment soon. Feel free to offer any comments or to report any Windows related bugs or issues. Because PreceptorTools has not been tested thoroughly in the Windows environment you should expect to encounter some bugs.\
\
If you fail to install PreceptorTools according to the directions above it will not function properly. Place the stacks in the locations specified in the installation directions above and everything will work fine. Learning modules and Generic modules created with PreceptorTools can be located anywhere on your hard drive.\
\
The Objects contained in the PreceptorTools Object Toolkits will not function in stacks other than PreceptorTools modules. While you may be able to place them in non PreceptorTools stacks this is strongly discouraged and may cause your stacks to malfunction. Finally, we will not answer support questions regarding the use of PreceptorTools Objects with non-preceptorTools stacks.\
